"id": "a4-risk-shifting-senior-vs-junior",
"problem_text": "Firm Y has debt with face value $120 due in 1 year. It must choose between two mutually exclusive projects: Safe and Risky. Both require the same investment today and are financed entirely with existing capital (no new securities). Project Safe yields asset values of $160 (good) or $120 (bad) with equal probability. Project Risky yields $200 (good) or $40 (bad) with equal probability. The required return on assets is 10%. You are asked to (1) compute firm value and equity value under each project, (2) determine which project is better for the firm as a whole, and (3) explain why equity holders may prefer a project that reduces firm value (risk-shifting).",
"archetype": "A4-PriorityAndRiskShifting",
"solution_steps": [
{
"part": "Step 1 - Reconnaissance",
