"part": "Step 3 - Firm and Equity Values under Project Risky",
"prompt": "Compute firm value and equity value for the riskier project.",
"reasoning": "Same approach: compute firm value from expected payoffs, and equity value as the residual after paying debt.",
"calculation": "Project Risky asset payoffs at t=1:\n- Good: 200.\n- Bad: 40.\nExpected payoff = 0.5 * 200 + 0.5 * 40 = 120.\nFirm value:\n  V_risky = 120 / 1.10 ≈ 109.09.\n\nDebt payoffs:\n- Good: 120.\n- Bad: min(40, 120) = 40.\nDebt value:\n  P_D_risky = [0.5 * 120 + 0.5 * 40] / 1.10\n            = (60 + 20) / 1.10\n            = 80 / 1.10 ≈ 72.73.\n\nEquity payoffs:\n- Good: 200 − 120 = 80.\n- Bad: max(40 − 120, 0) = 0.\nEquity value:\n  P_E_risky = [0.5 * 80 + 0.5 * 0] / 1.10\n             = 40 / 1.10 ≈ 36.36.",
