"archetype": "A1-CapitalStructure",
"solution_steps": [
{
"part": "Step 1 - Reconnaissance",
"prompt": "How do I know this is a tax shield valuation problem?",
"reasoning": "The stem highlights permanent debt, an explicit tax rate, and default risk that can wipe out future tax savings. It asks for the present value of interest tax shields. This is a classic A1 tax shield valuation under risky debt.",
"calculation": "Signals:\n- Permanent debt (or long-lived debt), not just a one-off loan.\n- Explicit corporate tax rate τ.\n- Default probability and loss of future tax shields.\n- Question is 'what is the PV of tax shields?'\n=> A1: Capital Structure & Tax Shields with Risky Debt.",
"sanity_check": "Whenever you see 'value the tax shield' plus default probability, you’re almost certainly in an APV / tax shield sub-problem of A1."
