"calculation": "If:\n- V_U is the unlevered firm value (no debt),\n- PV(TS) = 40,\n- PV(distress costs) =, say, 15,\nthen the levered firm value would be:\n  V_L ≈ V_U + 40 − 15 = V_U + 25.\nSo leverage adds about $25 of value on net, given this debt level.",
"sanity_check": "If someone claimed that adding this debt created 'no value' under taxes, you could point to the non-zero PV(TS) of $40 as the tax benefit channel. The real question becomes whether distress and other costs erode that $40 by more or less than $40."
}
