"calculation": "If Firm T’s main business has β_A,core = 0.8 and WACC = 7%, but this new line of business has β_A,project = 1.2 with asset discount rate 9%, then using T’s 7% WACC to evaluate the project would systematically over-accept risky projects.\n\nCorrect approach:\n- Use 9% to discount the project’s free cash flows to all investors.\n- Then decide whether to fund it with D/E = 0.5 to achieve the 12% required return for equity implied by CAPM.",
"sanity_check": "If the exam question asks 'Which WACC should you use?', always check whether the project risk is like the firm’s existing assets or like a different comparable. Using the wrong WACC is one of the most heavily tested conceptual mistakes."
