"calculation": "Gains from project:\n- Firm value increases by ≈ 16.36.\n- Debt value increases by ≈ 109.09 − 90.91 = 18.18.\n- Equity value before financing cost increases by ≈ 36.36 − 18.18 = 18.18.\nHowever, equity must raise 20 to fund the project, and new investors get a fairly priced claim.\n=> Old equity net gain ≈ 18.18 − 20 ≈ −1.82.\n\nDebtholders enjoy a large benefit (their claim becomes risk-free) without paying for the project.",
"sanity_check": "In debt overhang, any project where equity’s net gain is negative will be blocked, even if NPV > 0. The exam’s conceptual takeaway: capital structure can distort investment decisions when existing debt is risky."
}
